  SECOPY Dn:[file1] Dm:[file2]

This command copies sectors from disk
or file to another disk or file. It
works only with 128 byte sector disks.
Disks are neither analyzed nor
formatted. Copying continues until a
read or write error occurs.

SECOPY D1: D8:
Copies sectors from D1: to D8:.

SECOPY D8: D4:>BACKUP>RAMDISK.DSK
Copies sectors from D8: into a file.

SECOPY D4:>BACKUP>RAMDISK.DSK D8:
Copies a file to the sectors of D8:.
